chunk_content: H E • Assessing the Clinic-Lab Interface: The number of specimens received for testing may be used in A conjunction with other indicators to monitor the clinic-lab interface. L How to collect: Which facilities are counted? T H Collect data for the LAB_PTCQI indicator, both laboratory and POCT, at facilities with PEPFAR- S supported laboratories or POCT sites. A PEPFAR-supported laboratory or testing site is defined as a Y facility that receives direct service delivery (DSD) or technical assistance for service delivery S improvement (TA-SDI) from PEPFAR, is the recipient of specimens from PEPFAR-supported clinics, T E and/or receives proficiency testing panels via PEPFAR support. See definitions for ‘laboratory’ and M ‘POCT site’ below.
